(16, 2, 'Technical Staff', '', '<h1 style=\"font-size: 16pt; line-height: normal; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: center; color: #555555;\">\r\n	Secretary</h1>\r\n<center style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: medium; line-height: normal;\">\r\n	<table bgcolor=\"#F0F0F0\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" width=\"350\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\" width=\"100\">\r\n					<strong style=\"color: #555555;\">Name:</strong></td>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					<span style=\"color: #555555;\"><strong>Vaska Lubenova</strong></span></td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					<strong style=\"color: #555555;\">Phone:</strong></td>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					965 24 84</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					<strong style=\"color: #555555;\">E-mail:</strong></td>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					<a href=\"mailto:vlubenova@tu-sofia.bg\">vlubenova@tu-sofia.bg</a></td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					<strong style=\"color: #555555;\">Room:</strong></td>\r\n				<td style=\"margin-left: 0px; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" valign=\"CENTER\">\r\n					1323</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n	</table>\r\n</center>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 160),
(18, 2, 'About the Faculty of Computer Systems and Control and Computer Systems Department', '', '<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">The fast development and the advances in the field of computer and information technologies as well as the very large number of IT companies that work in the area of development and application of computer and information technologies generates serious demand for high-qualified professionals in the computer science field that are able to use the recent technological innovations.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The interest in study in the Faculty &ldquo;Computer Systems and Control&rdquo; is very high in the last several years and increases each year due to the need of qualified computer engineers in all areas of application of the computer and information technologies: business, education, science, medicine, transport, etc.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The faculty &ldquo;Computer Systems and Control&rdquo; (FCSC) is founded in 1987 and is one of the biggest faculties at the Technical University of Sofia with long years of experience in training highly qualified professionals for the industry and the business.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The faculty comprises two departments: department &ldquo;Computer Systems&rdquo;, founded in 1969, and department &ldquo;Programming and Computer Technologies&rdquo;, founded in 1984. The department &ldquo;Programming and Computer Technologies&rdquo; is responsible for the education in programming and informatics for all programs and specialties at the TU-Sofia as well as the training of the students in one of the master degree specialties provided at the faculty. The Department &ldquo;Computer Systems&rdquo; (cs-tusofia.eu/cscience) offers bachelor and master degree education in 7 specialties and is aimed at providing the students with up-to-date knowledge in the field of computer engineering and competitive skills that are required for successful professional carrier.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The faculty staff comprises 23 professors &ndash; 3 full professors and 20 associated professors, 23 assistant professors and 11 assistants, 4 engineers and 8 technicians. More than 1600 students study in the faculty each year, about 1300 in bachelor degree specialties and more than 300 in master degree courses. About 40 Ph.D. students work on their theses in the faculty at the moment. Each year about 200 bachelor degree engineers and about 70 master degree engineers are graduated at the FCSC. The Bachelor and Master degree diplomas are recognized worldwide and are in full compliance with the laws and regulations of the European Union.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The lecturers in the faculty provide education in various specialized courses according to their research interests for other base faculties at he Technical University of Sofia (Faculty of Telecommunications, Faculty of Electronic Engineering and Technologies, Faculty of Electrical Engineering, Faculty of Transport, Faculty of Management) as well as in the three faculties for foreign language study (English Language Faculty of Engineering, Faculty of German Engineering Education and Industrial Management, French Language Faculty of Electrical Engineering). Faculty staff members are also involved in the training courses of the Postgraduate Department/Continuing Education Division as well as in the education of the Professional Secondary School of Computer technologies and Systems &ndash; Pravets.The lecturers in the faculty provide education in various specialized courses according to their research interests for other base faculties at the Technical University of Sofia (Faculty of Telecommunications, Faculty of Electronic Engineering and Technologies, Faculty of Electrical Engineering, Faculty of Transport, Faculty of Management) as well as in the three faculties for foreign language study (English Language Faculty of Engineering, Faculty of German Engineering Education and Industrial Management, French Language Faculty of Electrical Engineering). Faculty staff members are also involved in the training courses of the Postgraduate Department/Continuing Education Division as well as in the education of the Professional Secondary School of Computer technologies and Systems &ndash; Pravets.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	The faculty of Computer Systems and Control has about 20 research and training laboratories available for the training in the bachelor and master degree courses. The laboratories are equipped with up-to-date computers, specialized high-technology hardware, various peripheral devices, specialized software and laboratory kits. A laboratory &ldquo;Virtual screening and computer modeling for drug design&rdquo; were founded in 2007 and is equipped with 40 core computer cluster with the financial support of the research project funded by the Ministry of Education and Science, National Science Fund. In 2009 according to a joint project between Microsoft Bulgaria and FCSC &ldquo;Innovation Centre&rdquo; were established in one of the laboratories of the faculty which will be used for students labs and as well as staff training based on the recent innovations of the company. FCSC has close cooperation with many IT companies on Bulgaria aimed at providing high quality education and qualification and guarantees successful professional employment of the graduated computer engineers. FCSC has fruitful cooperation with many universities and institutes in Europe and has a very successful experience in students and staff motilities under Erasmus program. The faculty staff members and students has also participate in lots international and national research projects. The faculty organizes International Scientific Conference &ldquo;Computer Science&rdquo; that has been successful conducted four times (International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2004&rdquo;, Sofia, Bulgaria, 7th Dec. 2004, Second International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2005&rdquo;, Chalkidiki, Greece, 30th Sept. &ndash; 2nd Oct. 2005, Third International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2006&rdquo;, Istanbul, Turkey, 12th &ndash; 16th Oct. 2006, Fourth International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2008&rdquo;, Kavala, Greece, 17th &ndash; 20th Sept. 2008), Fifth International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2009&rdquo;, Sofia, 3rd &ndash; 5th Nov. 2009), Sixth International Scientific Conference &ldquo;ComputerScience&rsquo;2011&rdquo;, Ohrid, FYROM, 1st &ndash; 3rd Sep. 2011). The faculty &ldquo;Computer Systems and Control&rdquo; issues a periodical journal &ldquo;Computer and Communication Engineering&rdquo; where research papers in the field of computer systems and informational technologies are published. The academic environment in the Faculty &ldquo;Computer Systems and Control&rdquo; provides excellent opportunities to gain the relevant education, research knowledge and professional skills.</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 170),
(17, 2, 'Teaching Facilities', '', '<p>\r\n	<img src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/hall1216students.png\" style=\"width: 412px; height: 112px;\" /></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_ipv6.png\" style=\"float: left; margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 15px; width: 250px; height: 160px;\" />More than 550 students from the Technical University will be teached in a laboratory how to work with new internet by sixth generation (IPv6). This said the Deputy-Minister of Transport, Information Technology and Communications, Parvan Rusinov during the presentation of the technical equipment today. It is installed in the Faculty of Computer Systems and Management as continuation and second phase of the Project &ldquo;6Deploy&rdquo; of the European Commission.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	In theory the exhaustion of the addresses in the present version of the Internet Protocol will happen between 2011 and 2013, said Parvan Rusinov. Because of that there is a recommendation of the European Commission for a gradually transition to a new protocol with more addresses in the global network. The new computers and servers, sold by the major producers are compatible with IPv6. The administration and the companies must train their network experts in order to be prepared.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n	In a distance form of learning, the Bulgarian laboratory may prepare students from other faculties and universities as well as representatives of the business. Here can be trained free key IT experts of the public administration, said in conclusion the Deputy-Minister.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n	(<em><strong>Source</strong></em>: <a href=\"http://www.mtitc.government.bg/page.php?category=92&amp;id=4773\">http://www.mtitc.government.bg/page.php?category=92&amp;id=4773</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_cp.png\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_e-control.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 155px;\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_hpcs.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 153px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_ms.png\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_pe.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 124px;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lab_pip.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 133px;\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/pages/lecturehall1216.png\" /></p>\r\n', 'Yes', 180),
(19, 2, 'Academic Calendars', '', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Academic Year 2013-2014</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/AcademicCalendars/Academic_calendar2014_8sem_bachelors.pdf\">Bachelor &ldquo;Computer Science&rdquo; - Graduates</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Yes', 190),
(20, 2, 'Summer Internships', '', '<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/logos/sap.gif\" style=\"width: 156px; height: 81px; margin-right: 15px;\" /></td>\r\n			<td valign=\"top\">\r\n				<h1>\r\n					Student practice in SAP IT Company</h1>\r\n				<h3>\r\n					Fast Facts about SAP:</h3>\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>\r\n						<a href=\"http://cs-tusofia.eu/moodle/file.php/1/StudentPractice/Fast_Facts_Turkish.pptx\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">ppt presentation in Turkish</span></a></li>\r\n					<li>\r\n						<a href=\"http://cs-tusofia.eu/moodle/file.php/1/StudentPractice/Fast_Facts_English.pptx\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">ppt presentation in English</span></a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 200),
(22, 2, 'Admission Requirements for Bachelor Program &quot;Computer Science and Engineering&quot;', '', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Requirements for admissions</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Citizens of EU countries who have successfully completed their secondary education and possess a high school diploma that enables them to study at higher education institutions in the country where they have completed their secondary education can apply to the programs of specialty &quot;Computer Sciences&quot; by submitting a set of application documents. Documents required to apply:</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1. Application form, containing some brief biographical data and the label of the applicant&#39;s desired program.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	2. A cetified* copy of the Secondary School or College Diplomas and their Supplement(s).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	3. A document, issued by competent authorities, which testifies to the right of the applicant to further his/her education at university level in the country where they have completed their secondary school/college education.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	4. A Medical Certificate of Health issued within a month prior to the application date and verified by the competent authorities in the country from which the applicant submits his/her file.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	5. Four recent passport-size photographs.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	6. A photocopy of the page (or pages) of your passport / personal identification card that give your photo, name, date and place of birth and passport / ID card expiry date.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	7. An original report providing the official score of the preliminary English exam test**.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	8. A reference letter (or letters) in English or Bulgarian from an official of the faculty which you obtained in authority.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Note</strong>: Documents 1,2 and 3 should be translated, legally verified bt the consular service of Republic of Bulgaria in the country of issue. Only original seals and stamps are accepted.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	* Certified copies are copies with an official stamp to verify that copies are true copies of original documents.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	** The English language exam tests happen in the Technical University of Sofia.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>IMPORTANT</strong>: An input English exam test for the students who has gone of the preparatory level of education in the Technical University of Sofia is not required. The students, that had failed in English exam test, have opportunity for them to enroll for preparatory level of education, offered by the Technical University of Sofia. The preparatory course duration is one year (2 semesters) and the following disciplines are educated: English Language, Mathematics, Informatics, Theory of Electrical Engineering, Physics.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Contact information for&nbsp;admissions:</strong><br />\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr bgcolor=\"#FAFAFA\">\r\n			<td>\r\n				Computer Science Graduate Admissions<br />\r\n				Kl. Ohridski ave. #8<br />\r\n				TU-Sofia, Block 1<br />\r\n				Faculty of Computer Systems and Control<br />\r\n				Department of Computer Systems<br />\r\n				Sofia 1000, Bulgaria<br />\r\n				Email:&nbsp; <a href=\"mailto:sevinch_mehmed@tu-sofia.bg\">sevinch_mehmed@tu-sofia.bg</a><br />\r\n				Phone:(+359 2) 895172745</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 210),
(21, 2, 'Admission Requirements for Master Program &quot;Computer Science and Engineering&quot;', '', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Requirements for Admissions and Application Procedure</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"#AdmissionCriteria\">Admission Criteria</a><br />\r\n	<a href=\"#MinimumDegree\">Minimum Degree Requirements &amp; Required Records of Academic Work </a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"#DomesticApplicants\">Domestic Applicants</a> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&gt; Required records</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"#InternationalApplicants\">International Applicants</a> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">&gt; Required records</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"#LanguageProficiency\">Evidence of English Language Proficiency</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information, please contact our english programs coordinator <a href=\"http://81.161.243.12/cs.tu-sofia.bg/index.php/component/contact/contact/1\">Eng. Sevinch Mehmed</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Contact information for&nbsp;admissions:</p>\r\n<table border=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr bgcolor=\"#fafafa\">\r\n			<td>\r\n				Kl. Ohridski ave. #8<br />\r\n				TU-Sofia, Block 1. Room 1327<br />\r\n				Faculty of Computer Systems and Control<br />\r\n				Department of Computer Systems<br />\r\n				Sofia 1000, Bulgaria<br />\r\n				Email:&nbsp; <a href=\"mailto:sevinch_mehmed@tu-sofia.bg\">sevinch_mehmed@tu-sofia.bg</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a name=\"AdmissionCriteria\"></a>Admission Criteria</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Faculty of Computer Systems and Control offers admission to applicants who appear to have the highest potential for graduate study and who, with the benefit of a graduate education, are the most likely to contribute substantially to their academic or professional fields through teaching, research, or professional practice.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The minimum graduate admission requirements are:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #993300;\">(1) a bachelor&rsquo;s degree or recognized equivalent from an accredited institution;</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #993300;\">(2) a good scholastic average, usually a minimum grade-point average (GPA) of 4 (<em>Local grade</em>) or C (<em>ECTS Grade</em>);</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #993300;\">(3) enough undergraduate training to do graduate work in the field of Computer Science.</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Admission decisions are based on departmental review, using a combination of factors, including academic degrees and records, the statement of purpose, letters of recommendation, test scores, and relevant work experience.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a name=\"MinimumDegree\"></a>Minimum Degree Requirements &amp; Required Records of Academic Work</span></h3>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<strong><a name=\"DomesticApplicants\"></a>Domestic Applicants</strong></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Applicants must hold or expect to hold prior to the beginning of classes a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in &quot;Computer Science&quot;, &quot;Computer Systems and Technologies&quot;, &quot;Computer and Communication Technique&quot; from Technical University of Sofia or another accredited BG university.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If the applicant hold a bachelor&#39;s or master&#39;s degree in other professional fields of study like &quot;Natural Sciences&quot;, &quot;Engineering&quot;, &quot;Economics&quot;, &quot;Agricultural Science&quot;, &quot;Security and Defence&quot;, &quot;Education Sciences&quot;, &quot;Humanities&quot;, &quot;Social and Economic Sciences&quot;, &quot;Arts&quot;, he/she must pass one year preparatory course, before to continue with the master degree program &quot;Computer Science&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Required Records for Master&#39;s Degree Program in &quot;Computer Science&quot;:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A&nbsp;true copy of high school leaving certificate or diploma and/or transcript. Bulgarian high school diplomas are considered as true copies if certified by a notary. If you have attended TU-Sofia, you must request an official transcript from the university.&nbsp;Applicants who do not hold a high school diploma at the time of applying must present an official high school transcript. Transcripts are considered official if they bear an official high school stamp and the signature of the high school principal. Academic transcripts should include the high school&rsquo;s contact information. Records must list the subjects taken, grades earned or examination results in each subject, and certificates or diplomas <span>with a calculated annual grade point average (GPA).</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A copy of papers already published in refereed journals, conference proceedings in the area of computer science and technologies. A certificate for presented or accepted papers are required to be presented. (<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em>Optional </em></span>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Certificate of participation in research projects and contracts related to computer science and technologies. (<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em>Optional </em></span>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A receipt for paid state of fee application.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed application form. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_ApplicationForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed admission application form for elective courses and a course projects for the 1st Semester. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_AdmissionForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Required Records for Preparatory (Equalization) Course of study in &quot;Computer Science&quot;:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A&nbsp;true copy of high school leaving certificate or diploma and/or transcript. Bulgarian high school diplomas are considered as true copies if certified by a notary. If you have attended TU-Sofia, you must request an official transcript from the university.&nbsp;Applicants who do not hold a high school diploma at the time of applying must present an official high school transcript. Transcripts are considered official if they bear an official high school stamp and the signature of the high school principal. Academic transcripts should include the high school&rsquo;s contact information. Records must list the subjects taken, grades earned or examination results in each subject, and certificates or diplomas <span>with a calculated annual grade point average (GPA).</span></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A receipt for paid state of fee application.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed application form. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_ApplicationForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<a name=\"InternationalApplicants\"></a>International Applicants</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	Graduates of recognized academic institutions outside the Bulgaria should hold a degree equivalent to a BG bachelor&#39;s degree. Equivalency is determined by International evaluators in the Graduate Admissions Office.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If the applicant hold a bachelor&#39;s or master&#39;s degree in other professional fields of study like &quot;Natural Sciences&quot;, &quot;Engineering&quot;, &quot;Economics&quot;, &quot;Agricultural Science&quot;, &quot;Security and Defence&quot;, &quot;Education Sciences&quot;, &quot;Humanities&quot;, &quot;Social and Economic Sciences&quot;, &quot;Arts&quot;, he/she must pass one year preparatory course, before to continue with the master degree program &quot;Computer Science&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Required Records for Master&#39;s Degree Program in &quot;Computer Science and Engineering&quot;:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A&nbsp;true copy of high school leaving certificate or diploma and/or college transcript. Non-Bulgarian diplomas are considered true copies if certified by an Apostille. Applicants who do not hold a high school diploma at the time of applying must present an official high school transcript. Transcripts are considered official if they bear an official high school stamp and the signature of the high school principal. Academic transcripts should include the high school&rsquo;s contact information. Records must list the subjects taken, grades earned or examination results in each subject, and certificates or diplomas <span>with a calculated annual grade point average (GPA). </span>If the documents are not in English, they must have a certified English translation accompanying them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A copy of papers already published in refereed journals, conference proceedings in the area of &quot;Computer Science and Technologies&quot;. A certificate for presented or accepted papers are required to be presented. (<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em>Optional </em></span>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Certificate of participation in research projects and contracts related to computer science and technologies. (<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em>Optional </em></span>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A receipt for paid state of fee application.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed application from. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_ApplicationForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed addmission application form for elective courses and a course projects for the 1st Semester. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_AdmissionForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Required Records for Preparatory (Equalization) Course of Study in &quot;Computer Science and Engineering&quot;:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A&nbsp;true copy of high school leaving certificate or diploma and/or college transcript. Non-Bulgarian diplomas are considered true copies if certified by an Apostille. Applicants who do not hold a high school diploma at the time of applying must present an official high school transcript. Transcripts are considered official if they bear an official high school stamp and the signature of the high school principal. Academic transcripts should include the high school&rsquo;s contact information. Records must list the subjects taken, grades earned or examination results in each subject, and certificates or diplomas <span>with a calculated annual grade point average (GPA). </span>If the documents are not in English, they must have a certified English translation accompanying them.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		A receipt for paid state of fee application.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Filled and signed application form. (<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/MCSC_ApplicationForm.dot\">Download</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a name=\"LanguageProficiency\"></a>Evidence of English Language Proficiency</span></h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	All applicants from countries in which the official language is not English are required to submit official evidence of English language proficiency.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If the applicant have completed at least one year of full-time academic course work with grades of B (Very Good) or better in residence at a university, he/she do not need to take a standardized test.</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 220);
INSERT INTO `pages_translations` (`page_id`, `language_id`, `title`, `short_description`, `content`, `active`, `position`) VALUES
(27, 1, 'Правила за класиране', '', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Класиране за ОКС магистър по &quot;Компютърно и софтуерно инженерство&quot;, едногодишно обучение</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Състезателният бал (изчисляван по точкова система) се образува от:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Средният успех от дипломата за образователно-квалификационна степен бакалавър, умножен по&nbsp;<strong>10&nbsp;</strong>. Максимален брой точки &ndash;&nbsp;<strong>60&nbsp;</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Оценката от дипломната работа, умножена по&nbsp;<strong>2&nbsp;</strong>. Максимален брой точки &ndash;&nbsp;<strong>12&nbsp;</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Сумата от оценките по&nbsp;<strong>3 предмета&nbsp;</strong>, изучавани в курса на обучение за степен &bdquo;бакалавър&rdquo;: &bdquo;Математика 1&rdquo;, &bdquo;Математика 2&rdquo; и &bdquo;ПИК 1&rdquo;. Максимален брой точки &ndash;&nbsp;<strong>18&nbsp;</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Защитена дипломна работа на първа сесия за защита за текущата учебна година в спец. &bdquo;КСИ&rdquo;&nbsp; и &quot;ИТИ&quot; в ТУ-София &ndash;<strong>&nbsp;6&nbsp;</strong>точки<strong>.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Завършена бакалавърска степен спец. &bdquo;КСИ&rdquo; и &quot;ИТИ&quot; в ТУ-София &ndash;&nbsp;<strong>3</strong>&nbsp;точки.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Участие в научна конференция, публикувани статии в реферирани списания у нас и в чужбина, свързани с компютърните технологии. Статиите задължително трябва да са рецензирани. Не се приемат статии, публикувани в пресата. Всяка статия носи по една точка. Участие в научни проекти и договори, свързани с компютърните технологии. Проектите и договорите трябва да бъдат с научен или научно-приложен характер. Не се зачитат чисто приложни системи. Максимален брой точки -&nbsp;<strong>1&nbsp;</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>МАКСИМАЛЕН БАЛ:</strong>&nbsp;100 точки.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Класиране за ОКС &bdquo;магистър&rdquo;, дугодишно платено обучение</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Състезателният бал се формира от средния успех от оценката на държавен изпит/дипломна работа.&nbsp;&nbsp;Минималният успех на кандидатите трябва да бъде добър.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Класиране за ОКС &bdquo;магистър&rdquo;&nbsp; след завършена степен &quot;професионален бакалавър&quot;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Състезателният бал се формира от средния успех на завършената бакалавърска степен &quot;професионален бакалавър&quot; и оценката на държавен изпит/дипломна работа. Минималният успех на кандидатите трябва да бъде добър.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Класиране за ОКС &bdquo;магистър&rdquo; след изравнително обучение&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Състезателният бал се формира от средния успех на завършеното изравнително обучение степен и оценката на държавен изпит/дипломна работа.&nbsp;&nbsp;Минималният успех на кандидатите трябва да бъде добър.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Класиране за ОКС магистър &quot;Графичен и web дизайн&quot;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Състезателният бал (изчисляван по точкова система) се образува от:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Средният успех от дипломата за образователно-квалификационна степен бакалавър, умножен по&nbsp;10&nbsp;. Максимален брой точки &ndash;&nbsp;60&nbsp;.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Оценката от дипломната работа, умножена по 5. Максимален брой точки: 30.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Завършена бакалавърска степен в сферата на графичния дизайн и изкуства: 5 точки.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Участие в научни проекти и договори, свързани с графичен дизайн и изкуства. Проектите и договорите трябва да бъдат с научен или научно-приложен характер. Максимален брой точки: 5.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 230),
(28, 1, 'Седмични разписи, Академична учебна година 2023/2024', '', '', 'Yes', 240),
(58, 1, '', '', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 540),
(29, 1, 'За контакти - магистри', '', '<table border=\\\"1\\\" cellpadding=\\\"3\\\" cellspacing=\\\"3\\\" frame=\\\"void\\\" rules=\\\"none\\\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"234\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					Длъжност</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"225\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					Лице за контакт</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"142\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					телефон</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"193\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					e-mail</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"234\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					Отг. маг. обучение катедра &ldquo;КС&rdquo;:</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"225\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					Ирина Георгиева</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"142\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					02 965 2484</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td valign=\\\"top\\\" width=\\\"193\\\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					<font color=\\\"#6a006a\\\">irina@tu-sofia.bg&nbsp;</font></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 250),
(32, 1, 'Процедура за кандидатстване на място', '', '<div align=\"\\&quot;center\\&quot;\">\r\n	<p>\r\n		За специалности:</p>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n			&quot;Компютърно и софтуерно инженерство&quot; - Редовно държавна поръчка</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n			&quot;Компютърно и софтуерно инженерство&quot; - Редовно платено обучение</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<p align=\"\\&quot;center\\&quot;\">\r\n	<strong><em>За кандидатстване в ОКС &quot;магистър&quot; специалност &quot;КСИ&quot;&nbsp; едногодишно обучение</em></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Заявление по образец</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; попълнено ръчно, подписано с отбелязана дата. В случай на ръчно попълване, трябва да попълните всички оцветени полета.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p align=\"\\&quot;center\\&quot;\">\r\n	Завършилите специалности , &bdquo;КСИ&ldquo; и &quot;ИТИ&quot; ОКС &quot;бакалавър&quot; във ФКСТ при ТУ-София, заверяват заявлението в учебната канцелария и не представят копие от диплома за степен &quot;бакалавър&quot;, академична справка или уверение.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Заявление за избираеми дисциплини и курсов проект през 1 семестър.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>За специалност &ldquo;КСИ&rdquo; - копие от диплома</strong>&nbsp;за завършена ОКС &bdquo;бакалавър&rdquo;&nbsp; от всички професионални направления от област 5. Технически науки, професионално направление 4.5 Математика, професионално направление 4.6 Информатика и компютърни науки&nbsp; или&nbsp;Академична справка&nbsp;при условие, че дипломата още не е издадена.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Копие от статии</strong>, отпечатани в реферирани периодични издания и сборници на научни конференции в областта на компютърните технологии. Ако статиите са приети за печат се представя служебна бележка&nbsp;<strong><em>&ndash; за спец. &bdquo;КСИ&ldquo;.</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Служебна бележка </strong>за участие в научни проекти и договори, свързани с компютърните технологии&nbsp;<em>&ndash; за спец. &bdquo;КСИ&ldquo;.</em></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Квитанция за платена държавна такса за кандидатстване</strong>.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<strong>Заявление за избираеми дисциплини, курсови работи и курсов проект подавате.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Приетите студенти в магистърските програми <strong>задължително при записването си ще попълват декларация с текст</strong>, че са запознати<strong>,</strong> че МАГИСТЪРСКАТА програма е с РЕДОВНА форма на обучение и присъствието на лекции и упражнения /от понеделник до петък/ е ЗАДЪЛЖИТЕЛНО /съгл. чл.90, ал.1, т.3, Раздел Четвърти от ПУиД на ТУ-София/.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Документите се подават в каб. 1201, с работно време понеделник-петък от 09.30 до 16.30 ч в срок от 09.09.2025 до 30.09.2025 г. вкл. Телефон за връзка 02 965 25 24.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 280),
(37, 1, 'Обява', '', '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/announcement-red.png\" style=\"width: 60px; height: 45px; float: left; margin-right:30px;\" />\r\n				<p>\r\n					&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<strong><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Кандидат-студентски прием в магистърски програми за новата учебна 2014-2015 година</span></strong></p>\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>\r\n						<a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/page.php?id=35\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Срокове</span></strong></a></li>\r\n					<li>\r\n						За въпроси и контакти <a href=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/page.php?id=48\">тук</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				<p>\r\n					Обучението в магистърската програма по &quot;<strong>Информационни Технологии</strong>&quot; е организирано съвместно с водещи фирми от ИТ сектора и техни специалисти, които ще участват в учебния процес.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/Magistri_AplicationForms/Master-IT.png\" style=\"width: 630px; height: 603px;\" /></p>\r\n', 'No', 330),
(35, 1, 'Срокове', '', '<p>\r\n	Срокът за подаване на документи за всички специалности в ОКС &bdquo;магистър&ldquo; чрез конкурс по документи е от 11.09.2023 г. до 29.09.2023 г. вкл.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Yes', 310),
(35, 2, 'Deadlines', '', '', 'Yes', 400),
(72, 1, 'Академичен календар - абсолвенти', '', '<h2>\r\n	Учебна 2024/25 г.</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"/userfiles/2024_2025/img162.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">График ОКС &quot;бакалавър&quot; - абсолвенти,&nbsp;</a>специалност КСИ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Учебна 2023/24 г.</h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"/userfiles/20232024/grafik_bak_absolvent_2023-24_KSI_last.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">График ОКС &quot;бакалавър&quot; - абсолвенти,</a>&nbsp;специалност КСИ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	Учебна 2022/23 г.</h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<a href=\"/userfiles/20232024/grafik_bak_absolvent_2022-23_KSI_last.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">График ОКС &quot;бакалавър&quot; - абсолвенти </a>, специалност КСИ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n', 'Yes', 610),
(40, 1, 'Дейности', '', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>Проектът се осъществява с финансовата подкрепа на</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>Оперативна програма &bdquo;Развитие на човешките ресурси&rdquo;,2007-2013,</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>съфинансирана от Европейския социален фонд на Европейския съюз</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	Инвестира във вашето бъдеще!</p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"3\" style=\"width: 500px;\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				<img alt=\"\" height=\"85\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/ESF_logo_BG.jpg\" width=\"120\" /></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n				<img alt=\"\" height=\"82\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/EU_logo_BG.jpg\" width=\"105\" /></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.38in;\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h1>\r\n	Дейности:</h1>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Частично изграждане на инфраструктура за електронни форми на дистанционно обучение към университетския Център за образователни и иновационни проекти.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Създаване на учебна бакалавърска и магистърска програма по &bdquo;Компютърни науки&rdquo; с електронни форми на дистанционно обучение.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Платформа за управление на обучението и знанието и изграждане на хранилища за електронни ресурси.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Разработване на електронни форми на учебно съдържание.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Обучение на преподаватели, административен и технически персонал за създаване на електронно съдържание на учебни курсове и използване на различни видове услуги и инфраструктура.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Организиране на обучение на лица от целевите групи в различни електронни форми на дистанционно обучение.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.81in;\">\r\n	&ndash; Разпространение на резултатите от проекта.</div>\r\n', 'Yes', 360),
(41, 1, 'Информационни дни', '', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>Проектът се осъществява с финансовата подкрепа на</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>Оперативна програма &bdquo;Развитие на човешките ресурси&rdquo;,2007-2013,</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	<em>съфинансирана от Европейския социален фонд на Европейския съюз</em></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\">\r\n	Инвестира във вашето бъдеще!</p>\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"3\" style=\"width: 500px;\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				<img alt=\"\" height=\"85\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/ESF_logo_BG.jpg\" width=\"120\" /></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n				<img alt=\"\" height=\"82\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/EU_logo_BG.jpg\" width=\"105\" /></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:.38in;\">\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h1>\r\n	<strong><em>Информационен ден на 17.12.2012 год</em></strong>.</h1>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>На 17 декември тази година ФКСТ на ТУ-София проведе Информационен ден по проект </strong><strong>№</strong> <strong>BG051 PO001-4.3.04-0044</strong>, &bdquo;<strong>Формални и неформални електронни форми за дистанционно обучение по &bdquo;Компютърни науки&rdquo;&rdquo;</strong><strong>.</strong> Схемата, по която ще се реализира проектът е BG051 PO001-4.3.04 &ldquo;Развитие на електронни форми на дистанционно обучение в системата на висшето образование&rdquo;, с финансовата подкрепа на Оперативна програма &ldquo;Развитие на човешките ресурси&rdquo;, съфинансирана от Европейския социален фонд на Европейския съюз, чрез МОМН. Размерът на одобрената безвъзмездна финансова помощ е една от най-големите за този тип проекти: 790 628.81 лева.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ръководител на проекта е Деканът на Факултета по компютърни системи и управление (ФКСТ) на ТУ-София: проф. д-р инж. Огнян Наков.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	За по- качествено и гъвкаво дистанционно обучение през целия живот на човека, проектът&nbsp; има за цел&nbsp; създаване към Университетския център за образователни и иновационни проекти на високотехнологична инфраструктура, базирана на електронни ресурси, виртуални лаборатории, учебни програми и богато електронно учебно съдържание. Ще бъде изградена платформа за управление на обучението и знанието, както и&nbsp; хранилища за електронни ресурси. Ще се интегрирани софтуерни средства за разпознаване на образи, комуникационни канали и ще се създадат виртуални лаборатории, които да предоставят хардуерни и софтуерни ресурси с отдалечен достъп.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/info_1.jpg\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 225px;\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>\r\n	<strong><em>Информационен ден със студенти на 26.02.2013 год</em></strong>.</h1>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Факултетът по компютърни системи и управление (</strong><strong>ФКСТ</strong><strong>)</strong><strong>&nbsp; на Т</strong><strong>ехническия </strong><strong>У</strong><strong>ниверситет</strong><strong>-София&nbsp; </strong><strong>ще бъде </strong><strong>IT </strong><strong>лидер в областта на дистанционното обучение по Компютърни науки.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n	<strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cs.fcst.bg/userfiles/info_2.jpg\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 225px;\" /></strong></p>\r\n', 'Yes', 370),
(43, 1, 'Изпитна сесия - бакалаври', '', '<h1>\r\n	<b>График за учебната 2023/2024 година</b></h1>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Редовна сесия</b></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellpadding=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellspacing=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;width:\" table=\"\" th=\"\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дисциплина</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Преподавател</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дата за изпит</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Редовна сесия - абсолвенти</b></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellpadding=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellspacing=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;width:\" table=\"\" th=\"\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дисциплина</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Преподавател</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дата за изпит</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Поправителна сесия</b></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellpadding=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellspacing=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;width:\" table=\"\" th=\"\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дисциплина</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Преподавател</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дата за изпит</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Поправителна сесия - абсолвенти</b></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellpadding=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellspacing=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;width:\" table=\"\" th=\"\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дисциплина</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Преподавател</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дата за изпит</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	<b>Ликвидационна сесия</b></h2>\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellpadding=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" cellspacing=\"\\&quot;1\\&quot;\" scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\" style=\"\\&quot;width:\" table=\"\" th=\"\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дисциплина</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Преподавател</strong></th>\r\n			<th scope=\"\\&quot;col\\&quot;\">\r\n				<strong>Дата за изпит</strong></th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n				&nbsp;</td>\r\n